        "comment": {
            "name": "comment",
            "type": "com.atlassian.jira.issue.fields.CommentSystemField",
            "value": [
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/25689",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=matthew",
                        "name": "matthew",
                        "displayName": "Matthew Weier O'Phinney",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "But what if you're using a Regex route, and your route can end in a file suffix? It seems to me that this should be either (a) optional, and\/or (b) something defined in individual route assembly.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=matthew",
                        "name": "matthew",
                        "displayName": "Matthew Weier O'Phinney",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2008-11-05T08:25:08.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2008-11-05T08:25:08.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/35270",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=matthew",
                        "name": "matthew",
                        "displayName": "Matthew Weier O'Phinney",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Can you document any web servers with the behavior you describe?\r\n\r\nThe Y! page you link to says this:\r\n{quote}\r\nOne of the most wasteful redirects happens frequently and web developers are generally not aware of it. It occurs when a trailing slash (\/) is missing from a URL that should otherwise have one.\r\n{quote}\r\nPlease note the end of the phrase \"from a URL that should otherwise have one.\" I'd argue that ZF URLs should not -- only URLs that actually represent directories would, as if the directory does not exist, mod_rewrite then rewrites the URL to ZF -- and no redirect is performed.\r\n\r\nIf other web servers do not behave this way, we can certainly add a flag -- but I don't want to go to the effort if it's an edge case that nobody is actually encountering.\r\n\r\n",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=matthew",
                        "name": "matthew",
                        "displayName": "Matthew Weier O'Phinney",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-10-16T06:47:50.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-10-16T06:47:50.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/39000",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=ccppprogrammer",
                        "name": "ccppprogrammer",
                        "displayName": "Nikolay Goldschmidt",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "I wrote Zend_View_Helper_Url plugin for redirect with 301 code to url with trailing slash.\r\nBut I vote for additional option in FC.\r\nThanks.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=ccppprogrammer",
                        "name": "ccppprogrammer",
                        "displayName": "Nikolay Goldschmidt",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2010-03-05T07:03:27.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2010-03-05T07:03:27.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/39001",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=tfountain",
                        "name": "tfountain",
                        "displayName": "Tim Fountain",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "I agree with Matthew that ZF URLs should not generally end in a trailing slash, but it would be nice to have an option to include this incase you are redeveloping a site that has previously enforced trailing slashes and you want to preserve the URLs. I can't think of a good way to ensure that slashes are not added to URLs with file suffixes though.\r\n\r\nI'm curious how other frameworks handle this. This is certainly a problem in Ruby on Rails. From some searching it seems Django has an APPEND_SLASH configuration option although I'm not sure exactly when this applies.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=tfountain",
                        "name": "tfountain",
                        "displayName": "Tim Fountain",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2010-03-05T09:40:43.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2010-03-05T09:40:43.000+0000"
                }
            ]
        }
